= The Death of Gustav Stresemann

Gustav Stresemann, leader of the DVP and longtime foreign minister, has died at the tragically young age of 51. He was the primary force driving his party to support democracy and maintaining cooperation with the SPD; without him, the democratic forces in the Republic will be so much weaker.

A power struggle has erupted within the DVP over the party's future direction:

**The Democratic Wing** (Theodor Heuss, Julius Curtius) argues for maintaining Stresemann's legacy of republican cooperation and coalition politics with the SPD and Center.

**The Business-Nationalist Wing** (Ernst Scholz, Eduard Dingeldey) demands a rightward shift toward business interests, national opposition, and alignment with the DNVP.

[? if dvp_relation >= 60 : Our strong relationship with the DVP gives the democratic wing credibility. ?]
[? if dvp_relation < 40 : Our poor relationship with the DVP strengthens those who want to abandon cooperation with us. ?]
[? if in_grand_coalition or in_weimar_coalition : The current coalition experience shapes the party's internal debate. ?]
[? if unemployment >= 15 : The economic crisis empowers those demanding radical change. ?]
[? if nsdap_r >= 10 : The Nazi surge creates pressure on the DVP to compete for nationalist voters. ?]

- @dvp_decision: The DVP will decide its own path...

@dvp_decision
on-arrival: {!
// Calculate which faction wins based on multiple conditions
var democratic_points = 0;
var nationalist_points = 0;

// SPD relations factor
if (Q.dvp_relation >= 70) democratic_points += 25;
else if (Q.dvp_relation >= 50) democratic_points += 15;
else if (Q.dvp_relation >= 30) democratic_points += 5;
else if (Q.dvp_relation < 30) nationalist_points += 15;

// Coalition experience
if (Q.in_grand_coalition || Q.dvp_in_government === 1) {
    democratic_points += 20;
    if (Q.dvp_dissent < 2) democratic_points += 10; // Successful coalition
    else if (Q.dvp_dissent >= 2) nationalist_points += 10; // Failed coalition
}

if (Q.spd_toleration) {
    nationalist_points += 10; // No cooperation experience
}

// Economic conditions
if (Q.unemployment >= 12) nationalist_points += 20;
else if (Q.unemployment >= 8) nationalist_points += 10;
else if (Q.unemployment < 8) democratic_points += 10;

if (Q.inflation >= 5) democratic_points += 10;
if (Q.economic_growth < -2) nationalist_points += 15;

// Political climate
if (Q.nsdap_r >= 15) nationalist_points += 20;
else if (Q.nsdap_r >= 10) nationalist_points += 10;
else if (Q.nsdap_r < 5) democratic_points += 10;

if (Q.dnvp_relation >= 30) nationalist_points += 15;
if (Q.z_relation >= 40) democratic_points += 10;

// Pro-republic sentiment
if (Q.pro_republic >= 60) democratic_points += 15;
else if (Q.pro_republic < 45) nationalist_points += 15;

// If SPD has governed well
if (Q.spd_in_government && Q.budget >= 0 && Q.unemployment < 8) {
    democratic_points += 10;
}

// Business pressure
if (Q.capital_strike_progress >= 4) nationalist_points += 20;
else if (Q.capital_strike_progress >= 2) nationalist_points += 10;

// Reformist policies alienate business
if (Q.works_councils >= 2 || Q.welfare >= 2) nationalist_points += 10;

// Foreign policy success
if (Q.reparations_negotiation >= 2 || Q.young_plan_seen) democratic_points += 10;

// Base tendency - business wing slightly stronger
nationalist_points += 5;

// Determine outcome
if (democratic_points > nationalist_points + 10) {
    Q.dvp_right_shift = 0;
    Q.dvp_outcome = "democratic";
    Q.dvp_leader = "Curtius and Heuss";
    Q.dvp_relation -= 5; // Still some loss without Stresemann
} else if (nationalist_points > democratic_points + 10) {
    Q.dvp_right_shift = 1;
    Q.dvp_outcome = "nationalist";
    Q.dvp_leader = "Dingeldey and Scholz";
    Q.dvp_relation -= 15;
} else {
    // Close contest - compromise leadership but nationalist lean
    Q.dvp_right_shift = 1;
    Q.dvp_outcome = "compromise";
    Q.dvp_leader = "Curtius (nominally), but with Dingeldey's influence";
    Q.dvp_relation -= 10;
}

// Additional effects based on outcome
if (Q.dvp_right_shift) {
    Q.nationalism += 3;
    Q.dnvp_relation += 5;
    Q.z_relation -= 3;
    Q.capital_strike_progress -= 1; // Business pleased
    
    if (Q.in_grand_coalition || Q.in_weimar_coalition) {
        Q.coalition_dissent += 1;
    }
} else {
    Q.pro_republic += 2;
    Q.z_relation += 3;
}
!}
go-to: dvp_outcome_display

@dvp_outcome_display

= DVP's New Direction

[? if dvp_outcome = "democratic" : After weeks of internal struggle, **Julius Curtius** has emerged as the new DVP leader, with strong support from Theodor Heuss and the party's democratic wing. In a speech to the party congress, Curtius declared his commitment to continuing Stresemann's legacy of republican cooperation and constructive coalition politics. ?]

[? if dvp_outcome = "nationalist" : After a bitter internal struggle, the business-nationalist wing has triumphed. **Eduard Dingeldey** and Ernst Scholz now control the party apparatus. In a defiant speech, Dingeldey announced that the DVP would no longer be "hostage to socialist demands" and would pursue a "national-liberal" course aligned with business interests and the DNVP. ?]

[? if dvp_outcome = "compromise" : After an inconclusive internal struggle, a compromise has been reached. **Julius Curtius** becomes the nominal leader, but Eduard Dingeldey and the business-nationalist wing have secured effective control over party policy. The democratic wing remains, but weakened. ?]

